# ðŸ”¹ If upgrade() creates a table
# downgrade() must drop that same table.

# ðŸ”¹ If upgrade() adds a column
# downgrade() must drop that same column.

# ðŸ”¹ If upgrade() changes column name
# downgrade() must rename it back
# If upgrade() changes column name

# downgrade() must rename it back.

# ðŸ”¹ If upgrade() deletes something

# downgrade() must add it back.

# ðŸŒŸ WHY THEY MUST MATCH?

# Because Alembic must know:

# Action	What if we want to undo it?
# upgrade	use downgrade
# +1 version	-1 version
# apply changes	remove changes
# forward direction	backward direction

